# OpenCAL WiFi Configuration
# To connect to WiFi on first boot:
#   1. Copy this file to wifi.txt in this same directory
#   2. Fill in your network SSID and PASSWORD below
#   3. Safely eject the SD card and boot
#
# This file (wifi.txt) is automatically deleted after credentials are applied
# so your password does not remain in plaintext on the boot partition.
#
# To reconfigure WiFi after first boot, SSH in over Ethernet and run:
#   nmcli device wifi connect "YourSSID" password "YourPassword"

SSID=
PASSWORD=
